---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Contract-Driven Development — Eidos AGI"
  description="Contracts define what we want. Skills define how to get there. Only one of those survives as AI improves."
>
    <article class="prose-page">
      <header class="page-hero">
        <h1>Contract-Driven<br />Development</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">Define what you want. Let the model figure out how.</p>
        <span class="status-badge status-shipped">Shipped</span>
      </header>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>The bitter lesson</h2>
        <p>Richard Sutton's greatest contribution to computer science: general methods that leverage computation always beat hand-crafted human knowledge as compute scales.</p>
        <p>We taught a computer to play chess by giving it the rules (a contract) and a goal (win). We didn't give it opening theory, middlegame strategy, or endgame technique (skills). The system that learned without human strategy knowledge destroyed the one built on decades of human expertise.</p>
        <p>Skills are chess strategy books. Contracts are the rules of chess. One decays with every improvement in reasoning. The other is permanent.</p>

        <!-- Value over time diagram -->
        <div class="cdd-diagram cdd-diagram-wide">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 500 200" fill="none" role="img" aria-label="Graph showing contracts maintaining value as AI improves while skills decay">
            <!-- Axes -->
            <line x1="60" y1="170" x2="480" y2="170" stroke="var(--color-muted)" stroke-width="1" opacity="0.3"/>
            <line x1="60" y1="170" x2="60" y2="20" stroke="var(--color-muted)" stroke-width="1" opacity="0.3"/>
            <text class="cdd-axis" x="270" y="195" text-anchor="middle">AI capability</text>
            <text class="cdd-axis" x="20" y="95" text-anchor="middle" transform="rotate(-90 20 95)">value</text>

            <!-- Model markers on X axis -->
            <text class="cdd-tick" x="120" y="185" text-anchor="middle">GPT-3</text>
            <text class="cdd-tick" x="220" y="185" text-anchor="middle">GPT-4</text>
            <text class="cdd-tick" x="320" y="185" text-anchor="middle">Opus 4</text>
            <text class="cdd-tick" x="420" y="185" text-anchor="middle">AGI</text>

            <!-- Contracts line (stays high) -->
            <path d="M 80 50 Q 200 45 320 40 Q 400 38 460 35" stroke="var(--color-command)" stroke-width="2.5" fill="none"/>
            <text class="cdd-line-label" x="465" y="30" fill="var(--color-command)">contracts</text>

            <!-- Skills line (decays) -->
            <path d="M 80 55 Q 200 80 280 110 Q 360 140 460 160" stroke="var(--color-danger)" stroke-width="2.5" fill="none" stroke-dasharray="6 3"/>
            <text class="cdd-line-label" x="465" y="158" fill="var(--color-danger)">skills</text>
          </svg>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Skills vs contracts</h2>
        <p>The AI ecosystem is building skills — step-by-step instructions that tell models how to accomplish goals. Skills work today. They compensate for what the model can't figure out on its own.</p>
        <p>But skills are written based on today's weaknesses. Go back two years. A skills file for GPT-3 would be extremely verbose — spelling out every step, every edge case, every format detail. Today's models need less. Tomorrow's models need even less. <strong>Skills are technical debt that accrues as models improve.</strong></p>

        <div class="cdd-changes">
          <div>
            <h3>A skill (150 lines)</h3>
            <div class="cdd-code">
              <pre><code>Step 1: Read CLAUDE.md
Step 2: Read .visionlog/vision.md
Step 3: Detect project type
  - Knowledge forge: skip performance
  - Software: check builds
Step 4: Score each dimension 1-10
  Use this rubric:
  | Dimension | 1 | 5 | 10 |
  | Reliability | ... | ... | ... |
Step 5: Pick the highest-impact gap
Step 6: Fix it
Step 7: Run tests
Step 8: Record the snapshot
  Use this JSON format:
  { "date": "...", "scores": {...} }</code></pre>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>A contract (10 lines)</h3>
            <div class="cdd-code">
              <pre><code>{
  "goal": "Leave the project measurably better",
  "output": "improvement-snapshot.schema.json",
  "constraints": [
    "Every score cites specific evidence",
    "Fix highest-impact gap, not easiest",
    "Never violate the project's guardrails",
    "Record every run"
  ]
}</code></pre>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p>The skill tells the model <em>how</em>. The contract tells it <em>what</em>. Models get better at <em>how</em> every six months. <em>What</em> doesn't change.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>A real example</h2>
        <p><a href="https://github.com/eidos-agi/eidos-assistant">Eidos Assistant</a> is a voice notes app with a Mac frontend (Swift), a classification daemon (Python), and an omni search adapter (Python). Three languages. Three processes. Five JSON Schema contracts hold it together:</p>

        <div class="cdd-contracts">
          <div class="cdd-contract">
            <h3>recording-bucket</h3>
            <p>What a voice recording looks like on disk. Audio, transcript, classification — each with defined fields, types, and enums.</p>
            <code>contracts/recording-bucket.schema.json</code>
          </div>
          <div class="cdd-contract">
            <h3>daemon-protocol</h3>
            <p>Request/response between the app and the classification daemon. What gets sent, what comes back.</p>
            <code>contracts/daemon-protocol.schema.json</code>
          </div>
          <div class="cdd-contract">
            <h3>adapter-manifest</h3>
            <p>How the app registers itself with the search engine. The app writes this on launch. The search engine reads it. Neither knows about the other's code.</p>
            <code>contracts/adapter-manifest.schema.json</code>
          </div>
          <div class="cdd-contract">
            <h3>manifest-entry</h3>
            <p>How recordings are tracked for discovery. The app appends entries. The search adapter reads them.</p>
            <code>contracts/manifest-entry.schema.json</code>
          </div>
          <div class="cdd-contract">
            <h3>performance-metric</h3>
            <p>How transcription speed is tracked over time. Every transcription logs duration, model, and real-time factor.</p>
            <code>contracts/performance-metric.schema.json</code>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Data flow diagram -->
        <div class="cdd-diagram cdd-diagram-wide">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 500 160" fill="none" role="img" aria-label="Data flow: voice recording flows through contracts between app, daemon, and search engine">
            <!-- App -->
            <rect class="cdd-pipe-node" x="10" y="20" width="100" height="50" rx="3"/>
            <text class="cdd-pipe-label" x="60" y="42" text-anchor="middle">Mac App</text>
            <text class="cdd-pipe-sub" x="60" y="56" text-anchor="middle">SWIFT</text>

            <!-- Bucket -->
            <rect class="cdd-pipe-node" x="145" y="20" width="100" height="50" rx="3"/>
            <text class="cdd-pipe-label" x="195" y="42" text-anchor="middle">Bucket</text>
            <text class="cdd-pipe-sub" x="195" y="56" text-anchor="middle">CONTRACT</text>

            <!-- Daemon -->
            <rect class="cdd-pipe-node" x="280" y="20" width="100" height="50" rx="3"/>
            <text class="cdd-pipe-label" x="330" y="42" text-anchor="middle">Daemon</text>
            <text class="cdd-pipe-sub" x="330" y="56" text-anchor="middle">PYTHON</text>

            <!-- Search -->
            <rect class="cdd-pipe-node" x="280" y="100" width="100" height="50" rx="3"/>
            <text class="cdd-pipe-label" x="330" y="122" text-anchor="middle">Omni</text>
            <text class="cdd-pipe-sub" x="330" y="136" text-anchor="middle">SEARCH</text>

            <!-- Arrows -->
            <line class="cdd-pipe-arrow" x1="110" y1="45" x2="145" y2="45"/>
            <polygon class="cdd-pipe-head" points="139,39 149,45 139,51"/>

            <line class="cdd-pipe-arrow" x1="245" y1="35" x2="280" y2="35"/>
            <polygon class="cdd-pipe-head" points="274,29 284,35 274,41"/>

            <line class="cdd-pipe-arrow" x1="245" y1="55" x2="280" y2="125" />
            <polygon class="cdd-pipe-head" points="273,121 283,127 276,131"/>

            <!-- Contract labels -->
            <text class="cdd-contract-label" x="195" y="85" text-anchor="middle">recording-bucket.schema.json</text>
            <text class="cdd-contract-label" x="330" y="85" text-anchor="middle">daemon-protocol.schema.json</text>
            <text class="cdd-contract-label" x="220" y="105" text-anchor="start">adapter-manifest.schema.json</text>
          </svg>
        </div>

        <p>Any AI model — current or future — can participate in this system by reading the contracts. The contracts tell it what data to produce. The model figures out how. The app also has skills. Those skills work today. They'll be unnecessary when models can infer the workflow from the contracts alone. The contracts will still be there.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>The confidence model</h2>
        <p>Every fact an agent depends on carries a confidence level. The readiness of a system is the lowest confidence level of its parts. One "unknown" field means the system is not production-ready, even if 99% is proven.</p>
        <table class="cdd-table">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Level</th><th>Meaning</th><th>Can build on?</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td class="cdd-level cdd-proven">proven</td><td>Tested in production, confirmed working</td><td>Yes</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="cdd-level cdd-tested">tested</td><td>Validated against real system</td><td>Yes, with monitoring</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="cdd-level cdd-researched">researched</td><td>From documentation, not verified</td><td>Verify first</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="cdd-level cdd-inferred">inferred</td><td>Guessed from similar systems</td><td>No — must verify</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="cdd-level cdd-unknown">unknown</td><td>No information available</td><td>No — must discover</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>The trilogy implements it</h2>
        <div class="cdd-diagram">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 500 80" fill="none" role="img" aria-label="Trilogy pipeline: research.md earns decisions, visionlog records contracts, ike.md executes within them">
            <rect class="cdd-pipe-node" x="10" y="15" width="140" height="50" rx="3"/>
            <text class="cdd-pipe-label" x="80" y="45" text-anchor="middle">research.md</text>
            <text class="cdd-pipe-sub" x="80" y="32" text-anchor="middle">EARN DECISIONS</text>

            <rect class="cdd-pipe-node" x="180" y="15" width="140" height="50" rx="3"/>
            <text class="cdd-pipe-label" x="250" y="45" text-anchor="middle">visionlog</text>
            <text class="cdd-pipe-sub" x="250" y="32" text-anchor="middle">RECORD CONTRACTS</text>

            <rect class="cdd-pipe-node" x="350" y="15" width="140" height="50" rx="3"/>
            <text class="cdd-pipe-label" x="420" y="45" text-anchor="middle">ike.md</text>
            <text class="cdd-pipe-sub" x="420" y="32" text-anchor="middle">EXECUTE</text>

            <line class="cdd-pipe-arrow" x1="150" y1="40" x2="180" y2="40"/>
            <polygon class="cdd-pipe-head" points="174,34 184,40 174,46"/>
            <line class="cdd-pipe-arrow" x1="320" y1="40" x2="350" y2="40"/>
            <polygon class="cdd-pipe-head" points="344,34 354,40 344,46"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="cdd-trio">
          <div class="cdd-trio-item">
            <h3>visionlog</h3>
            <p>Records the contracts — guardrails, goals, ADRs. The constraints all execution must honor.</p>
            <code>pip install visionlog-md</code>
          </div>
          <div class="cdd-trio-item">
            <h3>research.md</h3>
            <p>Earns decisions with evidence. Candidates scored against locked criteria. The research is the receipt.</p>
            <code>pip install research-md</code>
          </div>
          <div class="cdd-trio-item">
            <h3>ike.md</h3>
            <p>Executes tasks within the contracts. Definition of Done is explicit, not assumed.</p>
            <code>pip install ike-md</code>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>The transition</h2>
        <p>You don't have to abandon skills today. Current models still benefit from guidance. The shift is:</p>
        <ol class="cdd-steps">
          <li><strong>Define the contract first.</strong> What does the output look like? Write the JSON Schema.</li>
          <li><strong>Write the skill second.</strong> Only if the model can't meet the contract from the schema alone.</li>
          <li><strong>Test without the skill periodically.</strong> Give the model just the contract. If the output conforms, the skill is no longer needed.</li>
          <li><strong>Let skills decay.</strong> Don't maintain them. They're temporary bridges.</li>
        </ol>
        <p>The <code>contracts/</code> directory is permanent infrastructure. The <code>skills/</code> directory is a construction site that eventually gets torn down.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <p class="cdd-closing">Contracts define what we want, not how to deliver it. That's the primitive that survives AGI.</p>
        <pre><code>pip install visionlog-md research-md ike-md</code></pre>
      </section>

      <div class="related">
        <span class="related-label">Related</span>
        <div class="related-links">
          <a href="/trilogy">The Trilogy</a>
          <a href="/forges">Forges</a>
          <a href="/memory">Memory</a>
          <a href="/eidos">Eidos</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
</Base>

<style is:global>
  .cdd-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: var(--text-sm); margin: var(--space-6) 0; }
  .cdd-table th { text-align: left; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-xs); color: var(--color-muted); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-3); border-bottom: 2px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-muted) 20%, transparent); }
  .cdd-table td { padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-3); border-bottom: var(--border-width) solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-muted) 10%, transparent); color: var(--color-muted); }
  .cdd-level { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-weight: var(--weight-medium); }
  .cdd-proven { color: var(--color-command); }
  .cdd-tested { color: var(--color-secondary); }
  .cdd-researched { color: var(--color-primary); }
  .cdd-inferred { color: var(--color-muted); }
  .cdd-unknown { color: var(--color-danger); }
  .cdd-trio { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: var(--space-4); margin-top: var(--space-6); }
  .cdd-trio-item { background: var(--color-surface); padding: var(--space-6); border-radius: var(--radius-md); }
  .cdd-trio-item h3 { color: var(--color-primary); margin-bottom: var(--space-2); }
  .cdd-trio-item p { font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-muted); margin-bottom: var(--space-3); }
  .cdd-trio-item code { font-size: var(--text-xs); color: var(--color-command); }
  .cdd-changes { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: var(--space-6); margin: var(--space-8) 0; }
  .cdd-changes h3 { font-size: var(--text-base); margin-bottom: var(--space-3); color: var(--color-text); }
  .cdd-code { background: var(--color-surface); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: var(--space-4); }
  .cdd-code pre { margin: 0; font-size: var(--text-xs); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed); }
  .cdd-code code { color: var(--color-muted); }
  .cdd-contracts { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: var(--space-4); margin: var(--space-6) 0; }
  .cdd-contract { background: var(--color-surface); padding: var(--space-5); border-radius: var(--radius-md); }
  .cdd-contract h3 { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-primary); margin-bottom: var(--space-2); }
  .cdd-contract p { font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-muted); margin-bottom: var(--space-3); line-height: var(--leading-normal); }
  .cdd-contract code { font-size: var(--text-xs); color: var(--color-command); }
  .cdd-steps { padding-left: var(--space-6); }
  .cdd-steps li { font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-muted); padding: var(--space-2) 0; line-height: var(--leading-normal); }
  .cdd-closing { font-size: var(--text-md); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed); margin-bottom: var(--space-6); }
  .cdd-diagram { margin: var(--space-8) 0; max-width: 500px; }
  .cdd-diagram-wide { max-width: 540px; }
  .cdd-axis { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 9px; fill: var(--color-muted); letter-spacing: 0.05em; }
  .cdd-tick { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 8px; fill: var(--color-muted); }
  .cdd-line-label { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; font-weight: 500; }
  .cdd-contract-label { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 7px; fill: var(--color-command); opacity: 0.7; }
  .cdd-diagram svg { width: 100%; height: auto; }
  .cdd-pipe-node { fill: var(--color-surface); stroke: var(--color-primary); stroke-width: 1; }
  .cdd-pipe-label { font-family: var(--font-heading); font-size: 13px; fill: var(--color-text); font-weight: 500; }
  .cdd-pipe-sub { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 7px; fill: var(--color-primary); letter-spacing: 0.1em; }
  .cdd-pipe-arrow { stroke: var(--color-primary); stroke-width: 1.5; stroke-dasharray: 4 3; animation: conf-dash 1.5s linear infinite; }
  .cdd-pipe-head { fill: var(--color-primary); }
  @keyframes conf-dash { to { stroke-dashoffset: -14; } }
  @media (max-width: 768px) { .cdd-trio { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } .cdd-changes { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } .cdd-contracts { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } .cdd-table { font-size: var(--text-xs); } }
</style>
</Base>
